#: ../../014_release_schedule.md:1
msgid "Release Schedule"
msgstr ""

#: ../../014_release_schedule.md:2
msgid ""
"Updated: February 27, 2026<br><br> Starting in 2026, the release cycle "
"for FCS will change from the previous quarterly updates to semi-annual "
"updates in April and October (twice a year).<br>"
msgstr ""

#: ../../014_release_schedule.md:5
msgid "1. Regular releases (major versions)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../014_release_schedule.md:6
msgid ""
"Major versions that mainly include specification changes, such as adding "
"new features and changing algorithms, will be released twice a year, in "
"April and October.<br> By changing the release frequency, we aim to "
"further stabilize the quality of each version."
msgstr ""

#: ../../014_release_schedule.md:9
msgid "2. Hotfix releases (minor versions)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../014_release_schedule.md:10
msgid ""
"Once a major version is released, feature set is frozen until the next "
"regular release.<br> Minor version could include subtle improvements such"
" as UI refinement and bug fixes, will be released as needed (e.g., "
"24.10.01). <br>"
msgstr ""

#: ../../014_release_schedule.md:14
msgid "Upgrading FCS"
msgstr ""

#: ../../014_release_schedule.md:15
msgid ""
"We have discontinued dividing our products into different versions "
"(LTS/Standard/Preview) based on support status, etc. To simplify "
"operations, we have now standardized our format, providing all customers "
"with the same support period and the latest updates."
msgstr ""

#: ../../014_release_schedule.md:18
msgid "Compatibility"
msgstr ""

#: ../../014_release_schedule.md:19
msgid ""
"FCS sessions are forward-compatible unless explicitly noted otherwise; "
"however, backward compatibility is not always guaranteed, especially "
"across major versions (e.g., 25.07, 25.10).<br> This means you can open "
"FCS sessions created in a previous version of FCS using newer versions. "
"However, once a session is opened in a newer version, it may no longer be"
" possible to open it in an older version of FCS.<br> Therefore, it is "
"critical to back up your files before upgrading to a newer version of "
"FCS.<br> We strive to maintain backward compatibility within a major "
"version (e.g., across 25.10.01–25.10.04); however, this is not "
"guaranteed.<br>"
msgstr ""

#: ../../014_release_schedule.md:24
msgid "Steps to upgrade"
msgstr ""

#: ../../014_release_schedule.md:25
msgid "[Export your data](#export-header-target)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../014_release_schedule.md:26
msgid "Open the exported data using the newly downloaded version of FCS."
msgstr ""

